00:38:18.897 --> 00:38:20.465
You've been there too, yes?

00:38:20.465 --> 00:38:22.200
>> DANIELLE: Yes.

00:38:22.200 --> 00:38:25.850
I am a web developer so
I test very many forms

00:38:25.850 --> 00:38:28.220
and I do not enjoy it at all.

00:38:29.260 --> 00:38:32.420
>> MAXWELL: That's one of
the worst and especially

00:38:32.420 --> 00:38:36.430
because you're already invested
and it's also the worst

00:38:36.430 --> 00:38:39.340
for the website developer
because think about it this way.

00:38:39.340 --> 00:38:44.070
If I spend that time and get
to the end and I do reach out

00:38:44.070 --> 00:38:48.090
to you which there is no
guarantee I will reach out to you

00:38:48.090 --> 00:38:52.830
and if I do there's no guarantee
I won't use some negative language

00:38:52.830 --> 00:38:53.830
let's say.

00:38:54.730 --> 00:38:57.140
Think about it from
this point of view

00:38:57.140 --> 00:39:01.390
of your folks wouldn't it be easier
for your folks to get an email

00:39:01.390 --> 00:39:05.490
from somebody that wasn't already
wound up over an issue like this?

00:39:06.640 --> 00:39:11.520
It's in your best interest to test
the website form or anything else

00:39:11.520 --> 00:39:15.330
on your website because
you eliminate aggravation.

00:39:15.330 --> 00:39:17.300
You avoid hurt feelings.

00:39:17.300 --> 00:39:22.520
Trust me if any of you have watched
any of these police incidents

00:39:22.520 --> 00:39:24.640
that escalate quite
often they escalate

00:39:24.640 --> 00:39:26.760
because the people
involved are already upset.

00:39:28.690 --> 00:39:34.970
As a webmaster, we really want to
try to avoid making people upset

00:39:34.970 --> 00:39:37.620
without thinking about
it or for no good reason.

00:39:37.620 --> 00:39:42.190
I'd really have to be convinced
what their good reason would be

00:39:42.190 --> 00:39:43.600
to break something like the form.

00:39:45.230 --> 00:39:48.870
You're basically just saving
your team a bunch of aggravation.

00:39:48.870 --> 00:39:50.630
You may even be protecting.

00:39:50.630 --> 00:39:53.820
Actually, you could even
be protecting your brand

00:39:53.820 --> 00:39:59.240
by avoiding things like broken
forms and missing alt tags and links

00:39:59.240 --> 00:40:02.110
that I don't know are there because
they have no alt information.

00:40:02.110 --> 00:40:05.970
My screen reader can't find
the link so these things,

00:40:05.970 --> 00:40:09.320
they're small things
individually, but they add up.

00:40:09.320 --> 00:40:13.970
They're cabled up,
they show disrespect, and the more

00:40:13.970 --> 00:40:18.410
of them there are on your website,
your blog, your podcast player,

00:40:18.410 --> 00:40:22.970
et cetera, the more likely it is that
your tech support people are going

00:40:22.970 --> 00:40:25.290
to get a phone call or
they're going to get an email

00:40:25.290 --> 00:40:28.380
and they're going to walk away from
their computer and throw something

00:40:28.380 --> 00:40:31.290
or go to the break room and
get coffee because it's like,

00:40:31.290 --> 00:40:32.563
"Man, what did I do?"

00:40:32.563 --> 00:40:36.601
>> DANIELLE: [laughs]

