in WordPress or the block
editor to write posts?

00:44:49.910 --> 00:44:53.230
If there was a list of top things
you would like to see fixed

00:44:53.230 --> 00:44:56.040
in the admin,
what would be on that list?

00:44:56.040 --> 00:44:59.440
>> MAXWELL: I'm going to start by
saying something that may appear

00:44:59.440 --> 00:45:02.280
to be negative about
WordPress, but it's honest.

00:45:02.280 --> 00:45:05.720
That's my number one
guiding principle.

00:45:05.720 --> 00:45:08.430
I was not happy when
Gutenberg came around

00:45:08.430 --> 00:45:11.270
and we started adding all
this block editor stuff.

00:45:11.270 --> 00:45:15.520
I do run the classic
editor on my websites.

00:45:15.520 --> 00:45:19.630
Unfortunately, one of my websites
is been out there so long

00:45:19.630 --> 00:45:22.713
that even when I run
the classic editor,

00:45:22.714 --> 00:45:25.120
the block stuff still shows up.

00:45:25.120 --> 00:45:27.860
I have figured out how to
navigate the block stuff.

00:45:27.860 --> 00:45:34.250
I don't mind having to use the move
block up and move block down buttons.

00:45:34.250 --> 00:45:40.730
I've even figured out that if I
stop using double-line returns,

00:45:40.730 --> 00:45:45.730
then it'll stop adding paragraphs
when I where I don't want them.

00:45:45.730 --> 00:45:48.890
In general, I'm very happy that
they added the option of going back

00:45:48.890 --> 00:45:50.610
to the classic editor.

00:45:50.610 --> 00:45:54.080
I think for most people
that are running a one-page

00:45:54.080 --> 00:45:58.020
or less than five-page website
through their WordPress account,

00:45:58.020 --> 00:46:02.750
that classic editor is the
best simplest way to do it.

00:46:02.750 --> 00:46:05.310
Of course, you have to decide
on what plugins you're going

00:46:05.310 --> 00:46:07.120
to use beyond the classic editor.

00:46:08.520 --> 00:46:12.270
I'm still very happy with
WordPress because trust me,

00:46:12.270 --> 00:46:17.580
I coded my own code for seven
years and I still have nightmares.

00:46:17.580 --> 00:46:20.210
I'm very happy with WordPress.

00:46:20.210 --> 00:46:22.830
>> DANIELLE: You're optimistic
in the direction it's taking.

00:46:22.830 --> 00:46:26.510
If there were stuff that you
want to see fixed, what would be

00:46:26.510 --> 00:46:27.510
on that list?

00:46:28.260 --> 00:46:36.240
>> MAXWELL: I would say maybe
limiting or decreasing the number

00:46:36.240 --> 00:46:39.600
of items on the same
screen together.

00:46:39.600 --> 00:46:41.310
I find that one of the
things that bothers me

00:46:41.310 --> 00:46:44.970
as a screen reader user is
when I have too many options

00:46:44.970 --> 00:46:47.520
on the same screen together.

00:46:47.520 --> 00:46:51.240
For example,
when I open my WordPress dashboard,

00:46:51.240 --> 00:46:55.420
there's always the thanks
for using WordPress.

00:46:57.090 --> 00:47:00.650
There's stuff off to the top
left and the bottom right.

00:47:00.650 --> 00:47:07.100
I don't have a need to see as
I'm editing a post or a page.

00:47:07.100 --> 00:47:10.200
I'm thinking if there was a
way maybe a classic editor

00:47:10.200 --> 00:47:16.690
where I could press a key
command to just show me the stuff

00:47:16.690 --> 00:47:21.140
that's in play for what I'm doing,
I think that would be really cool

00:47:21.140 --> 00:47:24.210
because when you're using a screen
reader, the more objects there are

00:47:24.210 --> 00:47:27.550
on the screen, the longer it
takes you to find what you want

00:47:27.550 --> 00:47:32.100
to find and the longer it takes
you to navigate back and forth

00:47:32.100 --> 00:47:33.430
between those things.

00:47:33.430 --> 00:47:36.730
For example, I have a podcast.

00:47:36.730 --> 00:47:40.730
I produce a podcast and I've
helped other people start podcasts.

00:47:40.730 --> 00:47:45.200
I have the power press player
from blueberry.com installed

00:47:45.201 --> 00:47:46.690
on my websites.

00:47:46.690 --> 00:47:47.390
It works great.

00:47:47.390 --> 00:47:50.650
It's very accessible both on the
back end and when people come

00:47:50.650 --> 00:47:52.610
to listen to the podcast.

00:47:52.610 --> 00:48:00.040
I have to go from the, let's
see, upper third all the way down

00:48:00.040 --> 00:48:02.840
to near the bottom,
and I have to go back

00:48:02.840 --> 00:48:07.030
and forth and back and forth in
order to get the file uploaded

00:48:07.030 --> 00:48:12.330
to Blueberry the URL
from their site verified.

00:48:12.330 --> 00:48:13.880
It's just one of those things.

00:48:13.880 --> 00:48:16.930
If there was less real
estate to navigate,

00:48:16.930 --> 00:48:19.290
that would be a big
improvement in my opinion.

00:48:19.290 --> 00:48:22.280
>> DANIELLE: Back to that workflow
that you were talking about,

00:48:22.280 --> 00:48:25.390
if you do things in order,
put it in the order on the screen

00:48:25.390 --> 00:48:27.040
so you don't have to keep
going back and forth like that.

00:48:29.909 --> 00:48:31.370
>> MAXWELL: Yes.

